ROW.ENT:
Correct trend refers to a comparison of vibration amplitudes between different maneuvers; e.g., if the 1/rev vibration amplitude in the helicopter is higher during steady state turns than in level flight this increasing trend should be demonstrated in the simulator. Additional examples of vibrations may include:
(a) Low & High speed transition to and from hover;

(b) Level flight;

(c) Climb and descent (including vertical climb;

(d) Auto-rotation;

(e) Steady Turns.
